🔹 1. getLinks(Identity identity):-
👉 Ek user ke saare accounts (links) nikalta hai
List<Link> links = linkService.getLinks(identity);
✅ Output:-
[
  Link{id=1, app=AD, nativeIdentity=ksingh},
  Link{id=2, app=SAP, nativeIdentity=K123}
]

🔹 2. getLinks(Identity identity, Application application):-
👉 Specific app ka account
List<Link> links = linkService.getLinks(identity, app);
✅ Output:-
[
  Link{id=1, app=AD, nativeIdentity=ksingh}
]

🔹 3. getLink(Identity identity, Application application):-
👉 Ek hi link (single account)
Link link = linkService.getLink(identity, app);
✅ Output:-
Link{id=1, app=AD, nativeIdentity=ksingh}

🔹 4. getLinkById(String id):-
👉 DB id se link nikalta hai
Link link = linkService.getLinkById("123");
✅ Output:-
Link{id=123, app=AD, nativeIdentity=ksingh}

🔹 5. getLinkByNativeIdentity(Application app, String nativeIdentity):-
👉 Username se account find karta hai
Link link = linkService.getLinkByNativeIdentity(app, "ksingh");
✅ Output:-
Link{id=1, app=AD, nativeIdentity=ksingh}

🔹 6. getLinksByApplication(Application application):-
👉 Ek app ke sab users ke accounts
List<Link> links = linkService.getLinksByApplication(app);
✅ Output:-
[
  Link{user=A},
  Link{user=B},
  Link{user=C}
]

🔹 7. getLinksByIdentity(Identity identity):-
👉 Same as getLinks(identity)

🔹 8. getAccounts(Identity identity):-
👉 Accounts ka simplified version (mostly same as links)
List<Link> accounts = linkService.getAccounts(identity);

🔹 9. countLinks(Identity identity):-
👉 Kitne accounts hai user ke
int count = linkService.countLinks(identity);
✅ Output:-
2

🔹 10. createLink(Identity identity, Application application):-
👉 Naya account object banata hai (DB me abhi save nahi)
Link link = linkService.createLink(identity, app);
✅ Output:-
Link{unsaved object}

🔹 11. saveLink(Link link):-
👉 DB me save karta hai
linkService.saveLink(link);
✅ Output:-
Link saved in DB

🔹 12. deleteLink(Link link):-
👉 Account delete
linkService.deleteLink(link);

🔹 13. refreshLink(Link link):-
👉 Latest data sync karta hai (aggregation ke baad)
linkService.refreshLink(link);

🔹 14. getEntitlements(Link link):-
👉 Account ke access/groups
List ent = linkService.getEntitlements(link);
✅ Output:-
["Admins", "Users"]

🔹 15. setEntitlements(Link link, List entitlements);-
👉 Pura replace kar deta hai
linkService.setEntitlements(link, list);

🔹 16. addEntitlement(Link link, Entitlement ent):-
👉 Ek access add
linkService.addEntitlement(link, adminGroup);

🔹 17. removeEntitlement(Link link, Entitlement ent):-
👉 Access hata deta hai.

🔹 18. updateLink(Link link):-
👉 Link update karta hai
linkService.updateLink(link);

🔹 22. getDisabledLinks(Identity identity):-
👉 Disabled accounts
List<Link> list = linkService.getDisabledLinks(identity);
✅ Output:-
[Link{disabled=true}]

🔹 23. getActiveLinks(Identity identity):-
👉 Active accounts
List<Link> list = linkService.getActiveLinks(identity);
✅ Output:-
[Link{disabled=false}]

🔒 19. lockLink(Link link):-
👉 Iska kaam hai link ko temporarily lock karna, taki koi aur process usko modify na kare
🔧 Use case:-
2 process ek hi account update na kare
Data conflict na ho (race condition avoid)
💻 Code:-
linkService.lockLink(link);
🧠 Samajh:-
👉 Jaise tu ek file edit kar raha hai → lock lag gaya
👉 dusra banda edit nahi kar paayega
✅ Output (conceptual):-
Link{id=1} is LOCKED

🔓 20. unlockLink(Link link):-
👉 Lock hatata hai → ab koi bhi update kar sakta hai
💻 Code:-
linkService.unlockLink(link);
✅ Output:-
Link{id=1} is UNLOCKED

🔁 21. cloneLink(Link link):-
👉 Same link ka exact copy banata hai (new object, new id)
💻 Code:-
Link newLink = linkService.cloneLink(link);
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔍 2. searchLinks(QueryOptions options):-
👉 DB me filter laga ke links search karta hai.

🧠 Use Case:-
Specific condition pe data chahiye
Jaise: sirf AD accounts, ya disabled accounts
💻 Code:-
QueryOptions qo = new QueryOptions();
qo.addFilter(Filter.eq("application.name", "Active Directory"));
List<Link> links = linkService.searchLinks(qo);
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔗 1. mergeLinks(Link source, Link target):-
👉 Do links ko combine (merge) karta hai → ek hi account bana deta hai.
🧠 Use Case:-
Same user ke duplicate accounts aa gaye aggregation me
Data alag-alag links me split hai → ek me lana hai.

🧠 Samajh:-
👉 Before:-
Source Link:-
Link{id=1, app=AD, entitlements=[User]}

Target Link:-
Link{id=2, app=AD, entitlements=[Admin]}

👉 After merge:-
Target Link:-
Link{id=2, app=AD, entitlements=[User, Admin]}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔄 3. iterateLinks(QueryOptions options):-
👉 Ye bhi search jaisa hi hai — but large data ke liye optimized (streaming style)
🧠 Use Case:-
Lakho records ho DB me
Memory crash na ho → ek ek karke process karna
